You have an error in your regexp pattern.

You are using `\a` which matches the bell character (ASCII 7)

And `.` matches any character, you need to escape it.

Moreover, using both `use` and `loader` is misleading. You should use only one - see this answer:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41750715/when-do-i-use-use-and-loader-in-webpack-2-module-rules#answer-43842709

Try to use:
```js
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /app\.js$/i,
        loader: &#39;raw-loader&#39;
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

