By not specifying the type in the constructor, the generic type parameter is inferred to be `null`, not `User | null`. The type of the variable (`const user`) has no bearing on this (the assignment happens after the value construction and only performs a cast if any).

Explicitly specify the type of `T`:

    const user = new BehaviorSubject&lt;User | null&gt;(null);

