You are making it much more complicated that it really is!

You can use just the `SetPairingConfirmation()` function! You just have to make sure that you place a check to run the code if the API level is greater than 19 since `BluetoothDevice` was introduced only then. You might also want to use a different Exception catching like a `Java.IO.IOException`.
```
public bool IsPairingConfirmed(Android.Bluetooth.BluetoothDevice device)
{
    bool confirmation = false;
    try
    {
        if ((int)Android.OS.Build.VERSION.SdkInt &gt;= 19)
            confirmation = device.SetPairingConfirmation(true);
    }
    catch(Exception ex)
    {
        Console.WriteLine(ex.Message);
    }
    return confirmation;
}
```
I hope this makes sense, and make sure you do everything else right.

